1
00:00:18,442 --> 00:00:22,640
ORCHESTRA REHEARSAL

2
00:01:37,554 --> 00:01:40,352
Ooooh! Go on...

3
00:01:41,224 --> 00:01:42,316
...try it out

4
00:01:43,460 --> 00:01:45,325
The acoustics
are marvelous

5
00:01:46,630 --> 00:01:47,824
It was an ancient oratory

6
00:01:49,333 --> 00:01:52,393
Along there, are the tombs
of3 popes

7
00:01:52,769 --> 00:01:53,895
...and 7 bishops

8
00:01:55,906 --> 00:01:57,498
It's a graveyard in here

9
00:02:00,577 --> 00:02:02,545
In 1871...

10
00:02:03,280 --> 00:02:06,579
...this oratory became
a true auditorium

11
00:02:07,250 --> 00:02:09,616
...for both vocal
and instrumental concerts

12
00:02:10,153 --> 00:02:12,519
All the courts of Europe
envied us for it

13
00:02:13,190 --> 00:02:15,681
For its acoustics

14
00:02:16,760 --> 00:02:19,092
Ooooh, hear it?

15
00:02:19,596 --> 00:02:22,258
The sound is limpid,
without echo

16
00:02:22,633 --> 00:02:24,498
Ideal for listening
to music

17
00:02:25,335 --> 00:02:27,326
Without any reverberation

18
00:02:29,840 --> 00:02:30,670
That podium was...

19
00:02:31,408 --> 00:02:34,206
...for the world's
great conductors...

20
00:02:34,411 --> 00:02:35,639
...a mark of achievement

21
00:02:36,913 --> 00:02:38,073
What musicians!

22
00:02:38,515 --> 00:02:40,540
And the people!

23
00:02:40,917 --> 00:02:44,216
There were ministers,
ambassadors, clergy

24
00:02:44,454 --> 00:02:46,081
They'd bring their
own score...

25
00:02:46,556 --> 00:02:49,047
...to follow the music

26
00:02:50,694 --> 00:02:53,424
And what beautiful
ladies... elegant

27
00:02:53,864 --> 00:02:54,853
...audacious

28
00:02:55,999 --> 00:02:56,966
Playing tricks again?

29
00:02:59,002 --> 00:03:00,401
And the air was perfumed!

30
00:03:01,338 --> 00:03:02,771
...there was another
atmosphere...

31
00:03:03,507 --> 00:03:05,065
The public today is
no longer the same

32
00:03:05,709 --> 00:03:07,973
I must be boring you
with this chatter

33
00:03:14,051 --> 00:03:15,245
Everything is in place

34
00:03:17,421 --> 00:03:18,388
Beautiful, eh?

35
00:03:23,727 --> 00:03:26,958
But I'm only the copyist,
second fiddle to everyone

36
00:03:27,230 --> 00:03:27,992
Another year...

37
00:03:29,332 --> 00:03:31,061
... and off into retirement

38
00:03:33,570 --> 00:03:34,400
I'll return...

39
00:03:34,671 --> 00:03:36,332
...only to attend concerts

40
00:03:37,541 --> 00:03:38,337
That yes!

41
00:03:39,476 --> 00:03:40,841
I couldn't live
without music

42
00:04:08,739 --> 00:04:10,673
Good morning to one
and all!

43
00:04:11,041 --> 00:04:13,601
I heard some TV people
are coming to do...

44
00:04:13,777 --> 00:04:17,042
...a documentary about our
orchestra. This beautiful...

45
00:04:17,247 --> 00:04:20,478
...auditorium was once
a church

46
00:04:20,684 --> 00:04:22,379
...of the 13th century,
as you must know

47
00:04:22,652 --> 00:04:26,418
There, you can see
ancient tombs and...

48
00:04:26,590 --> 00:04:28,387
I already told them

49
00:04:29,359 --> 00:04:30,951
Oh, I'm the first violinist

50
00:04:31,495 --> 00:04:34,623
Good morning, Mirella

51
00:04:36,299 --> 00:04:38,859
Can somebody help with this
cover? It weighs a ton

52
00:04:39,069 --> 00:04:42,800
Here, let me

53
00:04:44,174 --> 00:04:47,200
Don't say anything.
TV people are here

54
00:04:51,314 --> 00:04:53,805
I'd like to know what
they do with these chairs!

55
00:04:54,951 --> 00:04:57,818
Dirty Filthy!

56
00:05:12,235 --> 00:05:12,758
They'll break!

57
00:05:15,405 --> 00:05:15,871
...Break wind!

58
00:05:17,674 --> 00:05:19,437
I'm having a sauna at 4,
no matter what

59
00:05:20,110 --> 00:05:23,102
...a snake, a lion... about
thirty positions in all

60
00:05:23,313 --> 00:05:26,510
...but it's all
a mental approach

61
00:05:26,817 --> 00:05:28,148
There's no hurry...

62
00:05:28,852 --> 00:05:30,046
...You're doing wonderfully

63
00:05:31,054 --> 00:05:33,284
To me he looks worse
than the last time

64
00:05:33,490 --> 00:05:37,358
Oh, Professor,
with us again!

65
00:05:38,295 --> 00:05:40,286
I'll bet the Professor
here...

66
00:05:40,697 --> 00:05:42,289
...that within 4 months...

67
00:05:42,632 --> 00:05:44,793
Professor, my
Uncle Quintilio...

68
00:05:45,268 --> 00:05:47,566
...ravished them all
for sixty years straight

69
00:05:47,871 --> 00:05:50,567
Big eater. Drinker.
Exceptional stud

70
00:05:51,575 --> 00:05:53,941
Everyone said:
he can't last

71
00:05:54,110 --> 00:05:56,476
Well, let me tell you,
he's 93

72
00:05:56,880 --> 00:06:00,646
...and still going strong

73
00:06:02,519 --> 00:06:03,918
"One of Werther's sons?"

74
00:06:04,421 --> 00:06:05,581
...begins with G

75
00:06:05,689 --> 00:06:08,157
What rotten people
you run into...

76
00:06:09,192 --> 00:06:11,660
...the light turned green

77
00:06:12,229 --> 00:06:14,197
...but he just stood there

78
00:06:14,898 --> 00:06:17,924
I tapped the horn and said
I was late for a rehearsal

79
00:06:18,368 --> 00:06:21,030
Then, as if eyeing a turd,
he says:

80
00:06:21,338 --> 00:06:23,568
"What's there to rehearse?
It's obvious..."

81
00:06:23,740 --> 00:06:25,332
"...you'll never learn"

82
00:06:29,646 --> 00:06:32,342
You're listening to the
soccer game? Not me...

83
00:06:32,549 --> 00:06:33,846
...I'm too nervous

84
00:06:34,451 --> 00:06:35,748
Your barometer?

85
00:06:36,019 --> 00:06:39,682
Let's see what old
faithful says

86
00:06:39,856 --> 00:06:41,983
Oh, it's gone up
another 15%%%

87
00:06:42,292 --> 00:06:45,386
...the prospects aren't
too good for my violin

88
00:06:45,829 --> 00:06:47,387
How's the octopus?

89
00:06:47,564 --> 00:06:50,226
Ah, it's a battle!
The thing's always there...

90
00:06:50,767 --> 00:06:52,200
...lying in ambush

91
00:06:52,402 --> 00:06:53,300
What a bitch!

92
00:06:53,837 --> 00:06:57,136
Go ahead keep up this shit
about my nightmares

93
00:06:57,974 --> 00:07:00,272
Don't get pissed, Professor,
it's bad for you

94
00:07:00,977 --> 00:07:04,140
Our neurosis is the
that's strangling us

95
00:07:09,019 --> 00:07:11,681
We paid a fortune for him,
but wasn't it worth it?

96
00:07:13,590 --> 00:07:14,056
What's that?

97
00:07:14,724 --> 00:07:17,158
A depressant

98
00:07:17,727 --> 00:07:19,285
I've tried them all,
no improvement

99
00:07:20,563 --> 00:07:21,791
...perhaps worse

100
00:07:25,502 --> 00:07:27,834
Why doesn't it play?
- look...

101
00:07:43,620 --> 00:07:45,053
Assholes!

102
00:07:45,288 --> 00:07:48,382
"8 and a Half" is a psycho-
analytical film? Get with it

103
00:07:48,591 --> 00:07:51,219
Brush up! What's with you?

104
00:07:51,528 --> 00:07:53,120
How can I play?
Hey, barometer...

105
00:07:54,030 --> 00:07:56,624
...put the chair where it
belongs so I can play

106
00:07:58,068 --> 00:07:59,968
No, sorry...
It's too close to the stand.

107
00:08:00,103 --> 00:08:02,162
I must sit there

108
00:08:02,605 --> 00:08:05,802
I must. Be courteous
I forgot...

109
00:08:05,976 --> 00:08:08,240
...my glasses

110
00:08:08,645 --> 00:08:11,705
I'm not here for courtesies,
but to play!

111
00:08:12,248 --> 00:08:13,715
I, here!

112
00:08:14,317 --> 00:08:15,147
I, there!

113
00:08:15,785 --> 00:08:17,218
This is my place

114
00:08:17,620 --> 00:08:19,520
You're offensive... THERE!

115
00:08:19,756 --> 00:08:20,313
...HERE!

116
00:08:21,024 --> 00:08:23,185
You sick in the head?...
Stop it!

117
00:08:23,393 --> 00:08:24,587
You stop!

118
00:08:42,379 --> 00:08:43,710
...your attention please

119
00:08:45,181 --> 00:08:46,944
A distinguished guest:

120
00:08:47,650 --> 00:08:48,446
...Television

121
00:08:49,119 --> 00:08:50,347
With technicians

122
00:08:50,987 --> 00:08:52,887
...and director,
for coverage

123
00:08:53,023 --> 00:08:54,183
...of our orchestra
rehearsal

124
00:08:55,759 --> 00:08:57,386
...And interviews

125
00:08:58,061 --> 00:09:00,052
You're better off if we're
not interviewed

126
00:09:00,597 --> 00:09:01,359
otherwise I'll tell

127
00:09:02,399 --> 00:09:03,491
Tell what?

128
00:09:04,100 --> 00:09:05,431
That you get a kickback

129
00:09:06,302 --> 00:09:08,566
For your participation

130
00:09:08,705 --> 00:09:10,195
...and your union
representative agrees...

131
00:09:10,340 --> 00:09:11,500
Compensation: nix

132
00:09:12,442 --> 00:09:14,342
No one made any agreement

133
00:09:15,545 --> 00:09:18,776
It's a special job!
For special rates!

134
00:09:19,249 --> 00:09:20,614
It's not special

135
00:09:20,917 --> 00:09:22,282
No, nothing doing!

136
00:09:23,319 --> 00:09:24,786
We're not in agreement

137
00:09:25,422 --> 00:09:27,481
Theoretically, we could
even accept

138
00:09:27,724 --> 00:09:29,351
...but not the Union

139
00:09:30,126 --> 00:09:31,991
It's the usual hedging
with State Television

140
00:09:32,162 --> 00:09:33,356
that's never solved

141
00:09:33,797 --> 00:09:35,731
Let your representative
tell you

142
00:09:36,266 --> 00:09:38,097
Calm down, people...

143
00:09:38,401 --> 00:09:40,631
We're already poorly paid...

144
00:09:40,870 --> 00:09:41,996
...but TV wants us
for nothing

145
00:09:42,205 --> 00:09:50,840
The public loves music
and the ones who play it.

146
00:09:51,481 --> 00:09:53,472
...but the minute it
becomes a program...

147
00:09:53,883 --> 00:09:55,817
For filming us, at least
a token

148
00:09:56,052 --> 00:09:56,814
...a gift

149
00:09:57,554 --> 00:09:59,021
No one is obliged

150
00:09:59,222 --> 00:10:01,622
...whoever grants
the interview

151
00:10:01,825 --> 00:10:03,486
...grants it. Who doesn't
want, doesn't grant

152
00:10:03,626 --> 00:10:04,149
How silly! Numbskulls!

153
00:10:04,360 --> 00:10:06,624
Allow me to turn your
attention to something...

154
00:10:06,796 --> 00:10:08,889
What kind of
representative are you?

155
00:10:15,271 --> 00:10:17,535
What an insult! Dumb heads!

156
00:10:21,244 --> 00:10:24,042
I dreamt there was a horse
in my room

157
00:10:24,447 --> 00:10:25,539
That's not good

158
00:10:26,049 --> 00:10:29,143
...Though it depends
on the horse's color

159
00:10:29,352 --> 00:10:30,046
Shitheads!

160
00:10:37,427 --> 00:10:39,019
You want to interview me?

161
00:10:40,463 --> 00:10:42,658
I prepared it

162
00:10:43,266 --> 00:10:44,824
...he helped me with it
through

163
00:10:46,236 --> 00:10:49,000
"The piano is like
a king on a throne"

164
00:10:49,272 --> 00:10:51,502
"Immobile. One must go to it"

165
00:10:51,741 --> 00:10:54,972
"Bow down. Near
the stool to it"

166
00:10:55,612 --> 00:10:58,604
"It's like a mythological
creature"... his doing

167
00:10:59,415 --> 00:11:04,546
"A room with a piano
becomes its room"

168
00:11:05,889 --> 00:11:07,948
"It's an instrument
of royal courts"

169
00:11:08,291 --> 00:11:10,589
What was that, Sir?

170
00:11:12,195 --> 00:11:14,755
I said I once played at court

171
00:11:15,131 --> 00:11:17,691
Before Victor Emanuel III

172
00:11:18,001 --> 00:11:19,434
And you weren't shot?

173
00:11:22,705 --> 00:11:26,232
I don't want a piano,
I mean I have one but...

174
00:11:26,442 --> 00:11:28,376
...it needn't be mine

175
00:11:28,711 --> 00:11:31,043
All the pianos of the world
are that piano

176
00:11:31,514 --> 00:11:33,573
To play mine alone...

177
00:11:33,917 --> 00:11:36,010
...would be limiting...
would be restrictive

178
00:11:36,586 --> 00:11:38,076
I think...

179
00:11:38,988 --> 00:11:42,014
...that to realize
one's self, one must...

180
00:11:42,358 --> 00:11:43,154
...be aware

181
00:11:44,594 --> 00:11:46,459
...that is, be more aware
of people

182
00:11:46,663 --> 00:11:49,325
...have more acquaintances

183
00:11:49,699 --> 00:11:52,327
Okay! I'm from
Marina di Pisa

184
00:11:53,069 --> 00:11:54,764
...but I took up the flute
in California

185
00:11:55,505 --> 00:11:57,302
...Where's it's played
sweeter, less violently

186
00:11:57,607 --> 00:12:00,007
The flute is a
delicate instrument

187
00:12:00,210 --> 00:12:03,008
The most similar to
the human voice

188
00:12:03,179 --> 00:12:06,637
Even if they say that
about the cello

189
00:12:06,816 --> 00:12:08,579
...and saxophone

190
00:12:08,751 --> 00:12:10,616
...and probably the drum!

191
00:12:12,855 --> 00:12:15,289
It's funny because
choral groups say...

192
00:12:15,425 --> 00:12:18,519
...they sound like an
instrument! But really...

193
00:12:18,695 --> 00:12:20,856
...only the flute has
that human quality

194
00:12:21,431 --> 00:12:24,628
What a mysterious sound...
supernatural!

195
00:12:25,201 --> 00:12:27,726
It even tames wild beasts

196
00:12:27,971 --> 00:12:30,405
Didn't Apollo use the flute
to awaken the dead?

197
00:12:31,341 --> 00:12:35,835
It's the instrument of magic
spells, both solar and lunar

198
00:12:36,045 --> 00:12:38,843
...why flutists are all
so batty

199
00:12:39,415 --> 00:12:42,350
It's true.
That's what they say

200
00:12:42,752 --> 00:12:44,913
Maybe because they blow
and blow...

201
00:12:45,255 --> 00:12:48,884
...and all that wind goes
to their heads, right?

202
00:12:49,659 --> 00:12:52,253
Everyone expects us to...

203
00:12:52,428 --> 00:12:54,521
...do something strange,
who knows why?

204
00:13:00,670 --> 00:13:02,433
The trombone is a
unique instrument

205
00:13:03,339 --> 00:13:06,206
...with a grave voice, that
admonishes with kindness

206
00:13:06,643 --> 00:13:10,374
And also very comical,
accompanying clowns

207
00:13:10,546 --> 00:13:12,377
...as they squirt water
and take falls

208
00:13:12,582 --> 00:13:14,243
It's the instrument
of angels!

209
00:13:14,417 --> 00:13:18,183
That's true, in Renaissance
paintings you'll see...

210
00:13:18,354 --> 00:13:19,412
...angels with trombones

211
00:13:19,622 --> 00:13:21,681
Received by the Lord
to trombone music...

212
00:13:21,858 --> 00:13:23,883
...fantastic

213
00:13:24,093 --> 00:13:25,754
The trombone
is the voice...

214
00:13:25,895 --> 00:13:27,362
...of a solitary being

215
00:13:28,064 --> 00:13:30,430
I love to listen to it
along the beach

216
00:13:30,633 --> 00:13:32,726
...in wintertime

217
00:13:56,893 --> 00:14:00,260
I have nothing to say,
really

218
00:14:00,496 --> 00:14:03,465
I was looking at that
hanging cobweb

219
00:14:03,833 --> 00:14:06,301
5 or 6 yards long,
isn't it?

220
00:14:06,569 --> 00:14:09,060
With the trombones blowing...

221
00:14:09,205 --> 00:14:11,867
...it swayed back and forth.
Look, look, see it?

222
00:14:12,075 --> 00:14:14,475
...the spider, up there?

223
00:14:14,677 --> 00:14:15,837
...hanging from the thread?

224
00:14:16,145 --> 00:14:18,773
See it?

225
00:14:19,816 --> 00:14:21,579
Isn't it wonderful
that we're here to make...

226
00:14:21,751 --> 00:14:24,117
...a spider go on a swing

227
00:14:24,520 --> 00:14:27,182
Take a look at it

228
00:14:27,523 --> 00:14:29,457
That little spider...

229
00:14:29,592 --> 00:14:31,389
...while the trombones
played...

230
00:14:35,264 --> 00:14:36,925
Can you spare a minute?

231
00:14:37,633 --> 00:14:38,827
...for a frivolous
question?

232
00:14:39,836 --> 00:14:42,066
Is it true there are likes
and dislikes

233
00:14:42,271 --> 00:14:43,829
between instruments?

234
00:14:44,507 --> 00:14:46,270
Absolutely, definite likes
and dislikes

235
00:14:46,442 --> 00:14:50,276
We get along with the bass

236
00:14:50,480 --> 00:14:52,948
...because it keeps time,
tight and even

237
00:14:53,116 --> 00:14:57,280
Without flourishes, trills
or "arpeggios"

238
00:14:57,487 --> 00:14:59,387
The piano is a chatterbox

239
00:14:59,622 --> 00:15:01,817
And violins bleed

240
00:15:01,991 --> 00:15:04,050
In Italy they concentrate
less on rhythm

241
00:15:04,827 --> 00:15:08,285
More on singing. Neapolitans
have a good sense of rhythm

242
00:15:08,498 --> 00:15:10,227
They're the best drummers

243
00:15:10,867 --> 00:15:12,528
Who invented the Tarantella?
The Neapolitans

244
00:15:12,902 --> 00:15:16,599
I'd say the rhythm
instruments...

245
00:15:16,639 --> 00:15:17,970
...are liked

246
00:15:18,007 --> 00:15:20,305
...they got humor.
Yeah, they're friendly

247
00:15:20,843 --> 00:15:22,606
What he says is true

248
00:15:22,745 --> 00:15:24,804
That air of sufficiency...

249
00:15:25,348 --> 00:15:26,747
The condescending tone...

250
00:15:27,617 --> 00:15:30,017
The haughtiness... of
a violin, or a flute

251
00:15:30,520 --> 00:15:33,318
...as it takes its place,
just doesn't exist with us

252
00:15:34,257 --> 00:15:35,918
Let a Neapolitan in
an orchestra...

253
00:15:36,092 --> 00:15:38,822
and what's he become?
The tympanist, the drummer

254
00:15:38,995 --> 00:15:41,691
...it makes him feel happy

255
00:15:41,931 --> 00:15:45,594
A little rhythm even helps
the Maestro...

256
00:15:45,768 --> 00:15:48,168
to get unwound.
Even the oboe

257
00:15:48,337 --> 00:15:50,168
forgets that it's gloomy,
and begins smiling

258
00:15:53,643 --> 00:15:56,168
I don't want to be
interviewed, or photographed

259
00:15:56,345 --> 00:15:59,178
I don't want to be mistaken
for someone else

260
00:16:01,150 --> 00:16:02,617
Try asking him

261
00:16:04,086 --> 00:16:04,745
Professor...

262
00:16:05,922 --> 00:16:07,685
Would you mind answering?

263
00:16:07,924 --> 00:16:09,516
Actually, you don't
deserve it

264
00:16:09,859 --> 00:16:12,020
Without compensation, I
shouldn't bother. However...

265
00:16:12,195 --> 00:16:14,129
...go ahead

266
00:16:14,497 --> 00:16:16,897
Let's see... Tell me
about your cello

267
