00:34:22,817 --> 00:34:24,842
Not he "couldn't", but
he "wouldn't" come...

536
00:34:25,086 --> 00:34:26,110
...in protest

537
00:34:26,855 --> 00:34:28,755
With the Union's approval

538
00:34:28,924 --> 00:34:30,789
So who plays,
somebody's sister?

539
00:34:31,493 --> 00:34:34,155
Leave our sisters alone

540
00:34:34,396 --> 00:34:35,886
...let's keep
the families out

541
00:34:36,197 --> 00:34:38,631
You said,
"somebody's sister"

542
00:34:38,900 --> 00:34:39,696
I only meant a...

543
00:34:40,802 --> 00:34:43,236
...hypothetical
saxhorn sister

544
00:34:43,505 --> 00:34:45,029
I don't grasp such subtle
humor

545
00:34:45,440 --> 00:34:48,409
You just worry about
your baton

546
00:34:48,643 --> 00:34:50,941
...and we'll take care
of our relatives

547
00:34:56,751 --> 00:34:58,309
All right then, from 5-2-0

548
00:34:58,753 --> 00:35:01,779
Not now

549
00:35:02,223 --> 00:35:03,622
The orchestra is upset

550
00:35:04,459 --> 00:35:06,393
...I doubt they can
continue rehearsing

551
00:35:09,664 --> 00:35:12,462
What the devil do you want
from me?

552
00:35:12,968 --> 00:35:15,596
See me lose my mind,
you want?

553
00:35:15,837 --> 00:35:17,361
You want my ass?

554
00:35:17,906 --> 00:35:19,464
Here, you got it!

555
00:35:24,579 --> 00:35:26,740
The orchestra will take
a double break

556
00:35:27,048 --> 00:35:27,776
...20 minutes

557
00:35:54,776 --> 00:35:57,040
The conductor? He's not
too bad

558
00:35:57,445 --> 00:35:58,639
Bit hysterical, but
within reason

559
00:35:58,847 --> 00:36:00,906
There's no need for
conductors like that

560
00:36:01,082 --> 00:36:03,380
A metronome's better

561
00:36:05,387 --> 00:36:07,821
The public should sit
in with us

562
00:36:07,989 --> 00:36:10,014
They'd hear the orchestra
as if watching a...

563
00:36:10,191 --> 00:36:12,489
...battle in a movie

564
00:36:12,861 --> 00:36:14,624
...or watching a real battle

565
00:36:15,363 --> 00:36:17,558
Ascetic. Tormented.
Authoritative

566
00:36:18,433 --> 00:36:21,596
Magnetic... the identity
of a great conductor!

567
00:36:21,836 --> 00:36:23,633
Then there are the mystics,
the priest-like

568
00:36:23,805 --> 00:36:24,794
The acrobatic

569
00:36:25,573 --> 00:36:27,905
How 'bout that lion tamer?

570
00:36:28,176 --> 00:36:31,339
He'd turn into a harp,
a violin, the drum

571
00:36:31,713 --> 00:36:34,181
...a kettledrum, even
the bassoon, what a riot!

572
00:36:34,382 --> 00:36:35,849
When there's a TV camera...

573
00:36:36,184 --> 00:36:37,412
... you can't shut up

574
00:36:38,319 --> 00:36:40,446
My Maestro up there
has to look at me

575
00:36:40,622 --> 00:36:42,146
...otherwise I'm jealous

576
00:36:47,395 --> 00:36:49,329
I'm on camera?

577
00:36:49,464 --> 00:36:51,830
"We're the lilies
of the valley"

578
00:36:52,500 --> 00:36:54,195
"We're pure Romans"

579
00:36:54,703 --> 00:36:56,967
...who's got friends?
Who sees anybody?

580
00:36:57,872 --> 00:37:00,204
You come in, punch a card

581
00:37:00,442 --> 00:37:01,739
...and pick it up later

582
00:37:01,910 --> 00:37:02,535
It's a factory

583
00:37:03,545 --> 00:37:04,011
Me?

584
00:37:05,013 --> 00:37:07,106
I thought I'd tour
the world with this

585
00:37:07,982 --> 00:37:08,971
...but I'm always here

586
00:37:10,418 --> 00:37:11,851
I'm sick of it...

587
00:37:12,387 --> 00:37:13,911
...this ridiculous
fart horn...

588
00:37:14,956 --> 00:37:17,220
It makes me feel useless,
it should be eliminated

589
00:37:17,992 --> 00:37:19,357
What's it good for?

590
00:37:19,961 --> 00:37:21,792
It can even be dangerous

591
00:37:21,963 --> 00:37:24,557
I give my all to shape
a sound

592
00:37:24,733 --> 00:37:27,793
...and out comes
another fart

593
00:37:29,404 --> 00:37:30,871
I think...

594
00:37:31,473 --> 00:37:33,998
...it's the very symbol
of obtuseness

595
00:37:34,242 --> 00:37:35,971
...of a stolid mentality

596
00:37:36,111 --> 00:37:38,477
Of those relationships...

597
00:37:39,114 --> 00:37:40,741
...in an orchestra,
that inhibit

598
00:37:42,250 --> 00:37:43,342
...any sort of contact

599
00:37:46,221 --> 00:37:48,189
I wanted to say that many
of us are from the provinces

600
00:37:48,623 --> 00:37:49,555
What province?...

601
00:37:50,492 --> 00:37:52,255
I'm from Naples:
"vaffanculo"

602
00:37:53,561 --> 00:37:55,290
The actual truth though

603
00:37:55,430 --> 00:37:57,193
...is that we're limited

604
00:37:57,999 --> 00:37:59,193
...culturally

605
00:38:00,068 --> 00:38:02,468
We've no real interests
in anything

606
00:38:02,604 --> 00:38:05,300
We spend our lives with
a piece of wood or tin

607
00:38:05,473 --> 00:38:07,839
...blowing away, or plucking

608
00:38:08,009 --> 00:38:10,807
Blow your philosophy
someplace else

609
00:38:12,380 --> 00:38:13,176
Anyway...

610
00:38:14,015 --> 00:38:15,141
All your gabbing about

611
00:38:16,151 --> 00:38:18,949
...Unions, the organic whole,
politics

612
00:38:19,320 --> 00:38:21,083
...brass section, strings

613
00:38:21,222 --> 00:38:23,213
...this or that conductor

614
00:38:23,391 --> 00:38:25,052
...couldn't interest me less

615
00:38:25,727 --> 00:38:29,390
Because I can't get it up
anymore

616
00:38:30,398 --> 00:38:31,228
That's the real tragedy

617
00:38:45,780 --> 00:38:48,408
Drink, drink, it's great
for the liver and the brain

618
00:38:49,584 --> 00:38:50,573
Just a drop of wine...

619
00:38:51,119 --> 00:38:52,518
...picks me up

620
00:38:52,854 --> 00:38:54,515
A little drop can't hurt

621
00:38:54,889 --> 00:38:58,825
It's whiskey, I saw it

622
00:38:59,027 --> 00:39:01,689
...and I even smell it

623
00:39:02,130 --> 00:39:06,328
Each to his own vices.
Better to drink...

624
00:39:06,534 --> 00:39:07,899
...than go molesting
little girls

625
00:39:08,837 --> 00:39:12,295
They'll catch you one day.
That's worse...

626
00:39:12,473 --> 00:39:12,962
...than whiskey

627
00:39:15,076 --> 00:39:16,839
I didn't choose the tuba

628
00:39:17,545 --> 00:39:18,842
...it chose me

629
00:39:19,981 --> 00:39:23,075
I loved the trumpet.
It gave me goose pimples

630
00:39:23,484 --> 00:39:25,179
You remember in the army...

631
00:39:25,420 --> 00:39:26,751
...when they played taps

632
00:39:36,531 --> 00:39:38,328
I'd get a lump in my throat

633
00:39:38,566 --> 00:39:40,659
...and then go AWOL.

634
00:39:40,902 --> 00:39:42,062
I'm very sensitive

635
00:39:42,637 --> 00:39:43,865
All art makes me cry

636
00:39:45,306 --> 00:39:46,330
And that's not all...

637
00:39:47,709 --> 00:39:49,267
At times I could die

638
00:39:49,811 --> 00:39:50,641
Why?

639
00:39:50,812 --> 00:39:54,077
The world is evil

640
00:39:54,983 --> 00:39:56,245
Now I miss my father!

641
00:39:57,051 --> 00:39:58,416
What the fuck you saying?

642
00:39:59,020 --> 00:40:01,011
Let's talk about
the instrument

643
00:40:01,422 --> 00:40:03,447
The fact that everybody
refused it, moved me

644
00:40:04,292 --> 00:40:06,123
Poor tuba... like a stray dog

645
00:40:06,494 --> 00:40:09,793
I felt akin to it

646
00:40:10,498 --> 00:40:11,465
...sad, and solitary...

647
00:40:12,100 --> 00:40:13,897
It's awkward like me

648
00:40:14,068 --> 00:40:16,696
We had to get together

649
00:40:17,272 --> 00:40:20,298
And we did. I did well,
it was destiny!

650
00:40:21,376 --> 00:40:22,673
...I'm attached to it

651
00:40:23,745 --> 00:40:24,734
...we're true friends

652
00:40:27,515 --> 00:40:29,983
When things are down
we go by the window

653
00:40:30,218 --> 00:40:32,152
...look up at the moon

654
00:40:33,421 --> 00:40:35,321
...and play a little solo
from Verdi

655
00:40:35,657 --> 00:40:37,887
Like to hear it? Eh?

656
00:40:38,993 --> 00:40:40,392
A little piece, why not

657
00:41:03,184 --> 00:41:05,744
People react and interpret
sounds, each in their own way

658
00:41:06,454 --> 00:41:07,785
It's a personal thing

659
00:41:08,156 --> 00:41:11,523
An F-sharp, or a B-flat

660
00:41:11,693 --> 00:41:13,320
...can make some
people swoon

661
00:41:14,362 --> 00:41:16,455
...and others vomit. That's
the way the ball bounces

662
00:41:17,131 --> 00:41:19,031
Yes, true

663
00:41:19,534 --> 00:41:21,502
What a magnificent
instrument the oboe is

664
00:41:22,370 --> 00:41:23,701
It's the oldest of all

665
00:41:24,472 --> 00:41:25,939
...invented by the Chinese

666
00:41:27,375 --> 00:41:28,307
The most difficult

667
00:41:29,277 --> 00:41:30,039
The most delicate

668
00:41:31,512 --> 00:41:32,444
...and most alone

669
00:41:33,247 --> 00:41:34,680
We oboists are isolated

670
00:41:35,249 --> 00:41:37,376
Envied, even disliked

671
00:41:39,087 --> 00:41:42,523
The orchestra has to reckon
with the oboe

672
00:41:43,725 --> 00:41:45,886
The oboe sets down the laws

673
00:41:46,127 --> 00:41:49,221
The oboe established
the diapason

674
00:41:49,530 --> 00:41:50,963
...between the highest pitch

675
00:41:51,733 --> 00:41:53,394
...and the lowest

676
00:41:54,335 --> 00:41:56,132
It's owing to this privilege

677
00:41:56,537 --> 00:41:58,164
...that the violin hates
the oboe

678
00:41:58,873 --> 00:42:02,741
...and the oboe the violin

679
00:42:03,444 --> 00:42:05,469
It's an instrument

680
00:42:08,616 --> 00:42:11,312
...of great spirituality

681
00:42:12,820 --> 00:42:14,617
He who plays it,
develops...

682
00:42:15,723 --> 00:42:17,418
...a sort of special power

683
00:42:19,994 --> 00:42:21,894
An interior vision

684
00:42:22,363 --> 00:42:23,625
...which permits him

685
00:42:24,365 --> 00:42:26,265
...to perceive the color
of sound

686
00:42:27,568 --> 00:42:28,330
I play...

687
00:42:29,437 --> 00:42:30,096
...and see

688
00:42:31,305 --> 00:42:33,000
...an aura of gold

689
00:42:33,608 --> 00:42:34,905
...luminous

690
00:42:35,143 --> 00:42:36,508
...the color of sunlight...

691
00:42:38,546 --> 00:42:40,639
like a spreading reflection
It's true...

692
00:42:41,182 --> 00:42:43,412
I once saw a thing...

693
00:42:43,684 --> 00:42:45,515
...like a long streamer

694
00:42:47,121 --> 00:42:49,783
A supernatural experience!

695
00:42:50,525 --> 00:42:53,016
Let him hear.
You care to hear?

696
00:42:53,227 --> 00:42:55,718
Certainly, if you're
not bored

697
00:43:05,907 --> 00:43:06,999
Maestro?... Excuse me

698
00:43:10,478 --> 00:43:11,445
Another minute...

699
00:43:12,213 --> 00:43:13,202
...he's taking a shower

700
00:43:15,616 --> 00:43:18,346
With the permanent conductor
they once had...

701
00:43:19,020 --> 00:43:21,011
...the musicians didn't
carry on like this

702
00:43:22,623 --> 00:43:24,113
Everyone wore a tie!

703
00:43:24,759 --> 00:43:26,852
You were in trouble
if you didn't

704
00:43:28,162 --> 00:43:31,825
Now I wouldn't be surprised
if they soaked their feet...

705
00:43:31,999 --> 00:43:34,058
...while playing.
We had a strict rule

706
00:43:34,235 --> 00:43:37,398
Whoever went flat
or missed his cue

707
00:43:37,972 --> 00:43:40,031
...had to play standing

708
00:43:40,475 --> 00:43:42,636
For the length of
the entire concert

709
00:43:43,044 --> 00:43:44,136
...as punishment

710
00:43:45,613 --> 00:43:48,548
What? Sessions? Hour shifts?

711
00:43:48,716 --> 00:43:50,149
...you worked all night

712
00:43:51,185 --> 00:43:53,483
Ah, how often I had to wait
till dawn

713
00:43:54,455 --> 00:43:56,855
And the musicians, at dawn,
dead tired...

714
00:43:57,825 --> 00:43:59,156
...would applaud
the conductor

715
00:43:59,827 --> 00:44:00,953
...and thank him

716
00:44:02,396 --> 00:44:03,886
Oh, he was phenomenal

717
00:44:04,999 --> 00:44:07,729
...he conducted with eyes
closed, as if in a trance

718
00:44:08,035 --> 00:44:10,196
...and yet saw everything.
How?...

719
00:44:13,541 --> 00:44:16,704
When he had to give a player
a calling down

720
00:44:17,378 --> 00:44:20,779
...he could find words
that would skin him alive

721
00:44:21,582 --> 00:44:23,550
And make him ill for a month

722
00:44:25,019 --> 00:44:27,510
And with his baton?
Such lashings...

723
00:44:27,688 --> 00:44:29,121
...on the hands and fingers
of those players

724
00:44:29,290 --> 00:44:30,814
who made a mistake

725
00:44:31,459 --> 00:44:33,427
It would hiss!

726
00:44:34,061 --> 00:44:37,428
Yet, you know something?
They were happy

727
00:44:38,166 --> 00:44:40,691
...for those hand raps

728
00:44:42,069 --> 00:44:44,128
They'd come up like
school children

729
00:44:45,106 --> 00:44:46,835
...hands held out and say:

730
00:44:47,275 --> 00:44:49,038
"My fault"

731
00:44:49,377 --> 00:44:51,436
"Hit me too... Me too,
I was wrong"

732
00:44:51,979 --> 00:44:53,844
Those were the days!

733
00:44:55,683 --> 00:44:57,548
You see what he's doing?

734
00:44:58,252 --> 00:44:59,913
TAKE YOUR STICK AND
CONDUCT MY PRICK

735
00:45:01,756 --> 00:45:02,723
You think that's right?

736
00:45:03,391 --> 00:45:04,858
Maybe now it's right

737
00:45:05,826 --> 00:45:06,952
No one knows anymore

738
00:45:15,436 --> 00:45:16,425
Maestro, there are...

739
00:45:17,305 --> 00:45:18,670
What else you want to know?

740
00:45:19,941 --> 00:45:22,466
I ask you: does music exist?
No?

741
00:45:22,910 --> 00:45:25,936
Then the world doesn't exist.
Only our habits do

742
00:45:26,113 --> 00:45:27,239
You may go...

743
00:45:30,218 --> 00:45:32,015
What meaning
has music today?

744
00:45:33,387 --> 00:45:36,322
You think people know
what music is?

745
00:45:37,491 --> 00:45:39,982
They consider themselves
intelligent because they feel

746
00:45:40,161 --> 00:45:42,755
...emotion in the gut.
They're participating

747
00:45:43,364 --> 00:45:46,197
Beethoven makes them feel
like knights in armor

748
00:45:48,336 --> 00:45:50,770
Some seem to be jumping out
of their seats

749
00:45:55,576 --> 00:45:57,567
When I'm conducting, I'm
always feeling ridiculous

750
00:45:59,947 --> 00:46:01,881
As if dead. I feel
like a ghost

751
00:46:02,583 --> 00:46:05,279
Better I don't say these
things. Cancel it!

752
00:46:06,187 --> 00:46:08,246
Today nothing is forgiven.
One must be...

753
00:46:08,556 --> 00:46:10,183
...always intelligent

754
00:46:11,225 --> 00:46:14,991
So let us say: music is...
...the world

755
00:46:15,463 --> 00:46:18,261
When I conduct I own
the world.

756
00:46:18,399 --> 00:46:19,627
I am a king

757
00:46:20,601 --> 00:46:23,161
You want to know really
how I feel?

758
00:46:24,372 --> 00:46:27,830
Like a sergeant who
must go kicking...

759
00:46:28,009 --> 00:46:28,634
...everybody in the ass

760
00:46:29,844 --> 00:46:31,971
But absurd laws forbid me...

761
00:46:32,146 --> 00:46:33,374
...to be a sergeant

762
00:46:35,349 --> 00:46:37,044
Certainly we have taken
advantage of

763
00:46:37,218 --> 00:46:38,515
our privileged positions

764
00:46:38,753 --> 00:46:39,720
Excuse me...

765
00:46:41,555 --> 00:46:42,681
Ach, warm as usual

766
00:46:43,224 --> 00:46:44,452
...no ice

767
00:46:46,794 --> 00:46:49,490
Talent is the child of whims
and eccentricity

768
00:46:51,799 --> 00:46:54,597
I once asked a musician
to remove his ring

769
00:46:54,769 --> 00:46:57,431
...the twinkling of the stone
bothered me

770
00:46:58,773 --> 00:47:02,038
And this seemed a caprice,
the whim of a divo

771
00:47:02,443 --> 00:47:03,410
That may even be

772
00:47:04,745 --> 00:47:07,339
But an exuberant character
for an artist

773
00:47:07,548 --> 00:47:10,073
...is a vital charge

774
00:47:10,251 --> 00:47:12,082
...for leading others,
for interpreting symphonies

775
00:47:12,920 --> 00:47:13,443
Prosit

776
00:47:17,992 --> 00:47:20,085
But now this unique charge
of the conductor

777
00:47:20,261 --> 00:47:21,023
is being contested

778
00:47:22,396 --> 00:47:23,192
The musicians?...

779
00:47:24,498 --> 00:47:26,125
...don't look at them,
don't see them

780
00:47:27,535 --> 00:47:29,901
Sometimes they have
unbearable face

781
00:47:32,139 --> 00:47:33,163
I'd put...

782
00:47:33,374 --> 00:47:35,842
...a screen in front
of some of them

783
00:47:37,011 --> 00:47:38,137
They're like wild dogs

784
00:47:39,213 --> 00:47:40,737
With wild eyes... No!

785
00:47:41,582 --> 00:47:42,606
Better cancel that too

786
00:47:44,118 --> 00:47:45,107
...or they shoot my legs

787
00:47:47,421 --> 00:47:49,412
The time of greatness
is "Kaputt"

788
00:47:52,493 --> 00:47:55,553
I remember the first time
I took my place at the podium

789
00:47:56,130 --> 00:47:58,724
My first, great impression
was...

790
00:47:58,966 --> 00:48:01,400
...the enormous silence
that fell before me

791
00:48:03,604 --> 00:48:04,969
As I signaled to begin...

792
00:48:05,973 --> 00:48:07,338
...I suddenly realized,
with great emotion,

793
00:48:07,742 --> 00:48:09,175
that my conductor's baton

794
00:48:10,077 --> 00:48:11,908
...was tied to the sound
of the orchestra

795
00:48:12,747 --> 00:48:14,214
Its voice came from within
my hand

796
00:48:15,516 --> 00:48:17,746
It would pull the orchestra
out of silence

797
00:48:18,152 --> 00:48:20,211
...and to silence make
it return

798
00:48:21,922 --> 00:48:24,322
This voice would rise...

799
00:48:24,492 --> 00:48:26,892
...like a sea wave
together with my arm

800
00:48:27,027 --> 00:48:29,757
...moving through the air
like a bird's wing

801
00:48:31,132 --> 00:48:34,499
And when my arm lowered,
this harmonic voice...

802
00:48:35,336 --> 00:48:36,428
...would fade again into
silence

803
00:48:39,039 --> 00:48:41,633
But now everyone is equal,
and I should resemble...

804
00:48:41,842 --> 00:48:43,969
...the first violinist
with his butcher's hands

805
00:48:45,379 --> 00:48:47,142
So I have fits of rage

806
00:48:48,182 --> 00:48:48,978
And buy houses

807
00:48:53,187 --> 00:48:53,915
Two in America

808
00:48:55,356 --> 00:48:57,347
One in Tokyo, in London,
and Berlin...

809
00:48:58,826 --> 00:49:01,124
In Paris, no houses.
That's because...

810
00:49:01,295 --> 00:49:04,355
I do not go along with
the music of France

811
00:49:05,266 --> 00:49:07,757
That's why, maybe,
the Customs at Orly...

812
00:49:08,302 --> 00:49:10,031
...is always frisking me

813
00:49:10,204 --> 00:49:12,468
...from head to foot

814
00:49:15,476 --> 00:49:17,535
You have your interview?
That's enough

815
00:49:19,647 --> 00:49:23,606
You say "the conductor"
but this word...

816
00:49:23,984 --> 00:49:24,814
...has no meaning anymore

817
00:49:26,220 --> 00:49:28,154
A true conductor is like
a priest

818
00:49:29,423 --> 00:49:30,947
He must have a church...
with believers

819
00:49:31,459 --> 00:49:35,486
...but when the faithful
all become

820
00:49:35,663 --> 00:49:36,561
...atheists...

821
00:49:37,898 --> 00:49:40,867
I remember Koplensky
my great maestro

822
00:49:41,836 --> 00:49:43,599
...I was first violinist

823
00:49:44,371 --> 00:49:46,498
When he took the podium,
everything was silence

824
00:49:47,274 --> 00:49:48,673
He would only look around...

825
00:49:49,376 --> 00:49:52,345
...distractedly.
But he already knew

826
00:49:52,513 --> 00:49:54,743
...every line of the score
in front of him

827
00:49:56,350 --> 00:49:58,011
He was music personified

828
00:49:59,019 --> 00:50:03,649
And we followed him happily,
with absolute reverence

829
00:50:03,824 --> 00:50:05,291
To enact the rite
of transubstantiation

830
00:50:06,360 --> 00:50:07,622
...to change the wine
into blood...

831
00:50:08,696 --> 00:50:09,628
...the bread into flesh...

832
00:50:10,764 --> 00:50:11,628
You laugh?

833
00:50:12,633 --> 00:50:13,361
...I hope not

834
00:50:14,969 --> 00:50:15,958
Music is always sacred

835
00:50:17,471 --> 00:50:18,665
Every concert is a Mass

836
00:50:20,908 --> 00:50:22,569
We were enthralled,
and we...

837
00:50:24,378 --> 00:50:26,403
...would forget
all worries...

838
00:50:26,647 --> 00:50:29,309
...at the first sign
of his baton

839
00:50:29,517 --> 00:50:32,350
...We were but one breath,
we and our instruments

840
00:50:32,653 --> 00:50:34,644
...a single vital force

841
00:50:35,956 --> 00:50:37,253
He would begin!

842
00:50:39,026 --> 00:50:40,618
Nothing was more beautiful
than his authority

843
00:50:42,796 --> 00:50:43,888
We trembled...

844
00:50:45,132 --> 00:50:45,860
...at the thought

845
00:50:47,434 --> 00:50:49,959
...of a mistake
in performing this rite

846
00:50:51,539 --> 00:50:53,029
An overwhelming emotion

847
00:50:53,874 --> 00:50:55,432
...an immense happiness

848
00:50:56,310 --> 00:50:58,369
We could feel...

849
00:50:58,646 --> 00:51:01,615
...our joy transmitting
itself

850
00:51:02,082 --> 00:51:05,051
...to the audience, which was
immobile, holding its breath

851
00:51:05,753 --> 00:51:08,415
We didn't watch the conductor
it wasn't necessary

852
00:51:09,356 --> 00:51:11,153
He was there, and we knew it

853
00:51:11,559 --> 00:51:12,890
...we felt it

854
00:51:16,997 --> 00:51:19,022
He was... within us

855
00:51:20,801 --> 00:51:22,701
...so much love passed
between him and us

856
00:51:24,738 --> 00:51:26,296
A love which you can see...

857
00:51:27,141 --> 00:51:28,165
...is now lost

858
00:51:30,844 --> 00:51:33,836
I and my musicians only feel
diffidence for each other

859
00:51:34,949 --> 00:51:36,644
The doubting...

860
00:51:36,884 --> 00:51:37,976
...which destroys belief

861
00:51:38,953 --> 00:51:41,547
And then there's a lack
of respect

862
00:51:41,689 --> 00:51:43,816
There's resentment. Because
something has been lost

863
00:51:43,991 --> 00:51:45,583
...never to be found

864
00:51:49,229 --> 00:51:50,423
That's how we play together

865
00:51:52,566 --> 00:51:55,091
United by a mutual hatred

866
00:51:57,204 --> 00:51:58,671
...like a family in ruin

867
00:52:24,031 --> 00:52:26,591
Maestro, the lights have
gone out

868
00:52:26,967 --> 00:52:27,592
I know

869
00:52:28,435 --> 00:52:29,197
What now?

870
00:52:30,404 --> 00:52:32,235
The break is over,
we rehearse!

871
00:52:38,078 --> 00:52:41,104
Go ahead, walk.
Light my way

872
00:52:51,959 --> 00:52:53,085
"Conductor, conductor..."

873
00:52:53,694 --> 00:52:54,888
"Conductor, no more!"

874
00:52:56,063 --> 00:52:57,894
"You'll only conduct us
Bowed to the floor"

875
00:53:22,156 --> 00:53:24,647
Claudio... you gotta
do something

876
00:53:30,698 --> 00:53:31,596
Now, the other eye!

877
00:53:32,099 --> 00:53:33,623
Boys, what are you doing?

878
00:53:35,169 --> 00:53:36,261
...listen

879
00:53:36,837 --> 00:53:38,498
"Conductor, conductor...
Conductor, no more"

880
00:53:39,173 --> 00:53:41,607
"You'll only conduct us
Bowed to the floor"

881
00:53:56,990 --> 00:53:59,618
Conductor no more!
No conducting allowed!

882
00:54:03,630 --> 00:54:04,688
We were idiots...

883
00:54:05,332 --> 00:54:06,390
...to study

884
00:54:07,568 --> 00:54:08,762
...to spend a lifetime
in a Conservatory

885
00:54:09,336 --> 00:54:10,360
That's right!

886
00:54:11,638 --> 00:54:13,697
We don't need conductors,
don't need music

887
00:54:14,108 --> 00:54:16,736
Nothing. Just a ring...

888
00:54:16,977 --> 00:54:18,274
...in our nose like savages

889
00:54:19,480 --> 00:54:22,074
Music is a public service.
It belongs to everyone

890
00:54:22,249 --> 00:54:23,841
Without class distinction

891
00:54:26,019 --> 00:54:27,213
Maestro...

892
00:54:27,955 --> 00:54:28,922
...how did this happen?

893
00:54:29,723 --> 00:54:31,281
"Conductor, conductor..."

894
00:54:31,925 --> 00:54:33,222
"Conductor no more"

895
00:54:34,294 --> 00:54:36,489
"You'll only conduct us
Bowed to the floor"

896
00:54:48,342 --> 00:54:50,276
What are you doing?

897
00:54:51,612 --> 00:54:52,601
You're crazy!

898
00:54:55,015 --> 00:54:55,481
How nice...

899
00:54:56,750 --> 00:54:57,546
...you're all sweated...

900
00:55:03,991 --> 00:55:05,686
"Conductor, Conductor..."

901
00:55:06,994 --> 00:55:08,120
What's falling here?

902
00:55:09,196 --> 00:55:12,188
What's happening?
- Worse yet, you're shifty,

903
00:55:12,232 --> 00:55:13,290
and corrupt. You've
been bought

904
00:55:13,333 --> 00:55:14,925
You signed too

905
00:55:15,169 --> 00:55:17,797
I'm reporting you the
Association. Immediately

906
00:55:18,105 --> 00:55:19,629
Down with music power!

907
00:55:20,274 --> 00:55:21,639
Down with assembly line
music!

908
00:55:22,376 --> 00:55:23,707
It's gotta stop!

909
00:55:24,578 --> 00:55:26,512
Stop!

910
00:55:33,020 --> 00:55:34,351
Take a look, what's
on my head?

911
00:55:36,223 --> 00:55:37,383
Let me taste

912
00:55:40,093 --> 00:55:41,617
What is it you want?

913
00:55:42,996 --> 00:55:44,486
Moron, it's raining!

914
00:55:44,865 --> 00:55:46,730
I'll not be insulted!

915
00:55:52,139 --> 00:55:53,106
What's he doing?

916
00:55:55,075 --> 00:55:57,100
Look at how one can
ruin his life...

917
00:56:00,614 --> 00:56:01,273
Again...

918
00:56:02,883 --> 00:56:03,372
Another?

919
00:56:08,322 --> 00:56:09,653
Down with the baton!

920
00:56:09,957 --> 00:56:11,390
Music belongs to us!

921
00:56:12,292 --> 00:56:14,726
You don't exist! Who is he?

922
00:56:14,995 --> 00:56:16,724
I ask you, who is he?

923
00:56:17,464 --> 00:56:20,331
He doesn't exist. And if
he does, he shouldn't!

924
00:56:27,140 --> 00:56:29,267
There's blood. Wretches!
Madmen!

925
00:56:29,476 --> 00:56:31,171
"You're fucked,
you're through"

926
00:56:31,345 --> 00:56:32,812
"It's all over for you"

927
00:56:34,147 --> 00:56:36,172
May I sit down for
the interview?

928
00:56:43,957 --> 00:56:45,481
I was first aware
of the harp...

929
00:56:46,260 --> 00:56:47,989
...in a dream.
I was very little

930
00:56:48,495 --> 00:56:51,328
I didn't know what
to think...

931
00:56:51,498 --> 00:56:53,796
...of that small gold cage

932
00:56:56,637 --> 00:56:58,195
One day, in a book...

933
00:56:58,272 --> 00:56:59,796
...I saw Nero, and Rome
that was burning

934
00:57:00,040 --> 00:57:02,975
...and the instrument
I had dreamt

935
00:57:04,511 --> 00:57:07,480
And then in a perfumed
calendar there was...

936
00:57:07,648 --> 00:57:10,640
...an angel flying and
he played the same harp...

937
00:57:10,951 --> 00:57:12,350
...of my dreams

938
00:57:13,387 --> 00:57:14,149
The harp!

939
00:57:14,588 --> 00:57:16,488
For me it's a human presence

940
00:57:17,157 --> 00:57:20,752
I couldn't live in a house
without a 60 harp

941
00:57:21,762 --> 00:57:23,821
I'd never fall asleep
if I didn't know...

942
00:57:24,865 --> 00:57:27,129
...it was nearby in
the next room

943
00:57:28,735 --> 00:57:30,999
At times hands seem
to run across it

944
00:57:31,972 --> 00:57:32,700
I hear it play

945
00:57:33,974 --> 00:57:34,770
...it could be the wind

946
00:57:43,550 --> 00:57:45,245
The harp is my very life

947
00:57:46,687 --> 00:57:48,450
Not only for what
I have earned

948
00:57:49,323 --> 00:57:50,756
...but it's my refuge

949
00:57:51,658 --> 00:57:52,454
...my friend

950
00:57:53,994 --> 00:57:56,792
I've always lived alone.
No men

951
00:57:57,731 --> 00:57:58,663
No one

952
00:57:59,399 --> 00:58:00,093
...only the harp

953
00:58:01,068 --> 00:58:02,660
We confide, we talk...

954
00:58:03,337 --> 00:58:05,532
...it answers me,
I receive sensations

955
00:58:05,973 --> 00:58:09,204
...fantasies... an
overwhelming sense of joy

956
00:58:09,876 --> 00:58:11,002
...and of sadness

957
00:58:12,145 --> 00:58:15,137
Mostly, it gives one...

958
00:58:15,415 --> 00:58:16,040
...faith

959
00:58:16,984 --> 00:58:17,973
You become aware...

960
00:58:18,151 --> 00:58:20,142
...that other
dimensions exist

961
00:58:25,058 --> 00:58:26,286
A child once asked:

962
00:58:26,493 --> 00:58:28,358
"Where does music go
when it's over?"

963
00:58:29,696 --> 00:58:31,323
...only a child could
ask that

964
00:58:33,033 --> 00:58:35,661
"Orchestra - terror
Conductor - death"

965
00:58:36,069 --> 00:58:38,970
"Orchestra - terror
Conductor - death"

966
00:58:39,539 --> 00:58:42,474
"Orchestra - terror
Who plays is a traitor"

967
00:59:06,800 --> 00:59:08,700
Here's our new conductor!

968
00:59:18,311 --> 00:59:19,938
Long live the Metronome!

969
00:59:21,615 --> 00:59:24,448
"Metronome metronomous...
Musicians - autonomous"

970
00:59:46,940 --> 00:59:49,704
"Musicians at last
freed from the past"

971
00:59:53,180 --> 00:59:55,273
Down with the metronome.
We'll establish...

972
00:59:55,415 --> 00:59:57,440
...the tempo, the rhythm,
the cadence

973
00:59:57,617 --> 01:00:01,314
We've had enough
of their music

974
01:00:01,555 --> 01:00:06,822
...it's degrading!
We play it, we'll create it,

975
01:00:06,993 --> 01:00:07,687
we'll manage it

976
01:00:08,562 --> 01:00:09,722
I'll not...

977
01:00:10,330 --> 01:00:11,797
...be directed by anyone!

978
01:00:11,998 --> 01:00:13,898
Death!

979
01:00:14,067 --> 01:00:14,897
...to the metronome!

980
01:01:09,656 --> 01:01:11,351
Idiot! Give me that gun

981
01:01:11,725 --> 01:01:12,521
...gimme

982
01:01:15,862 --> 01:01:18,353
You're hurting me.
I have a permit

983
01:01:19,166 --> 01:01:20,793
Look in my wallet

984
01:01:21,868 --> 01:01:23,233
All right let's see it

985
01:01:27,541 --> 01:01:28,701
...in his name

986
01:01:29,676 --> 01:01:32,907
A regular firearm permit

987
01:01:34,114 --> 01:01:34,808
Get up...

988
01:01:39,352 --> 01:01:40,114
A Smith & Wesson!

989
01:02:00,207 --> 01:02:02,767
Look up there... up there!

990
01:02:08,715 --> 01:02:09,409
Look!

991
01:02:17,290 --> 01:02:18,814
Everything's...

992
01:02:18,992 --> 01:02:19,890
...crumbling!

993
01:02:25,665 --> 01:02:26,529
Help me...

994
01:03:04,804 --> 01:03:05,566
Help me...

995
01:03:26,092 --> 01:03:26,786
Oh, why?

996
01:03:36,636 --> 01:03:37,500
...you are here...

997
01:03:39,139 --> 01:03:39,901
...and I'm here...

998
01:04:04,130 --> 01:04:06,598
Everyone must give undivided
attention to his instrument

999
01:04:08,735 --> 01:04:11,033
...that is all we can do now

1000
01:04:12,906 --> 01:04:14,305
Somebody can help me?

1001
01:04:15,008 --> 01:04:15,599
...please

1002
01:04:26,820 --> 01:04:28,310
The notes are saving us

1003
01:04:31,124 --> 01:04:32,022
Music saves us

1004
01:04:33,226 --> 01:04:34,352
Hang on to the notes

1005
01:04:37,430 --> 01:04:38,454
Follow the notes

1006
01:04:41,301 --> 01:04:42,290
...one after the other...

1007
01:04:43,970 --> 01:04:45,301
In the way my hand...

1008
01:04:46,673 --> 01:04:47,605
...can indicate

1009
01:04:49,909 --> 01:04:51,274
We are musicians...

1010
01:04:53,380 --> 01:04:55,075
You are musicians...

1011
01:05:07,026 --> 01:05:07,788
...and we're here

1012
01:05:08,728 --> 01:05:09,251
...to rehearse

1013
01:05:20,573 --> 01:05:22,632
Have no fear.
The rehearsal continues

1014
01:05:23,710 --> 01:05:24,642
To your places!

1015
01:05:25,512 --> 01:05:26,376
In place, please

1016
01:05:30,950 --> 01:05:31,644
...thank you...

1017
01:08:18,885 --> 01:08:21,183
You must do less coloring
with sounds

1018
01:08:21,588 --> 01:08:23,852
Noise is not music

1019
01:08:24,424 --> 01:08:26,085
Not a trolley car,
I heard pots and pans

1020
01:08:26,426 --> 01:08:28,223
Where are we?

1021
01:08:29,062 --> 01:08:32,225
...one a soccer field?
You think I'm an umpire?

1022
01:08:33,333 --> 01:08:35,062
And where has
the brass gone?

1023
01:08:35,435 --> 01:08:37,300
What's happened to
your little lungs?

1024
01:08:38,605 --> 01:08:39,936
Where is all your breath?

1025
01:08:40,773 --> 01:08:42,263
...used it for
stupid chatter?

1026
01:08:43,209 --> 01:08:44,267
Sustain the notes!

1027
01:08:57,290 --> 01:08:58,951
Gentlemen... DA CAPO!

